  "Title": "#使用GIT#git@oschina.net#.txt",
  "Text": "<p>基本使用</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>1. 工具: msysgit</p><p>2.方法:命令行，简单使用方法</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>easy to add information</p><p>====================================</p><p>git config --global user.name = tiny</p><p>git config -- global user.email = <a href=\"mailto:xxxxx@qq.com\">xxxxx@qq.com</a></p><p>====================================</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>check infomation</p><p>====================================<br></p><p>git config --global --list</p><p>====================================<br></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>easy to upload</p><p>====================================</p><p>①directory [A],right click&gt;&gt;git bash.</p><p>②git init</p><p>③copy files into this directory [A]</p><p>④git add .</p><p>⑤git commit (-v) or git commit -m \"this is single line of commit\"</p><p>[add some commit in the first line of vim]</p><p>⑥git remote add origin <a href=\"https://git.oschina.net/xxxx/xxxx.git\">https://git.oschina.net/xxxx/xxxx.git</a> &nbsp;</p><p>⑦git push origin master</p><p>====================================</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>easy to pull</p><p>====================================</p><p>cd to the directory you want to pull remote version to</p><p>①git init</p><p>②git remote add origin //if you have add a remote address ever, skip this step.</p><p>③git pull origin master &nbsp;// wherevery origin stands for server git version master stands for local branch version</p><p>====================================</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>easy to clone</p><p>====================================<br></p><p>mkdir &nbsp;you want</p><p>①mkdir [A];// cd into [A]</p><p>②git init</p><p>③git clone <a href=\"https://git.oschina.net/xxxxxxx/xxx.git\">https://git.oschina.net/xxxxxxx/xxx.git</a></p><p>====================================<br></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>easy to ssh [invalid]</p><p>===============================================</p><p>cd to the version you want</p><p>①ssh-keygen -t rsa -C \"xxxxxxx@qq.com\"</p><p>②input a name for your public key ie.[oschina_]</p><p>③input a password for your public key ie.[xxxxxx],input twince</p><p>④ssh-add oschina_.pub</p><p>⑤if error ocurrs:</p><p>$ ssh-add oschina_.pub</p><p>Could not open a connection to your authentication agent.</p><p>⑥ $ ssh-agent bash --login -i</p><p>Welcome to Git (version 1.8.3-preview20130601)</p><p>⑦ $ ssh-add oschina_</p><p>Enter passphrase for oschina_:</p><p>Identity added: oschina_ (oschina_)</p><p>⑧Add oschina_.pub to your account key &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;online &nbsp;manager page.</p><p>you will not need any username and password now!</p><p>===============================================</p><p>note:Adding rsa key can only pull and clone. It's a shame.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>easy to proxy</p><p>===============================================</p><p>git config --global http.proxy http://10.101.1.6:80</p><p>===============================================</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>easy to unproxy</p><p>===============================================</p><p>git --unset --global http.proxy</p>"
}
