  "Title": "Linux Mint Installing RHC, Configure it && Use SSH && modify Default Django App && Git Push With OpenShift Support",
  "Text": "<p>[Step 01.Setup Env]</p><p>Linux Mint Install RHC and Cconfigure &amp;&amp; Use SSH With OpenShift Support</p><p>$ sudo apt-get install ruby-full rubygems git-core<br></p><p>$ sudo gem install rubygems-update </p><p>$ sudo update_rubygems</p><p>$ sudo gem install rhc<br></p><p>$ rhc setup<br></p><p>...</p><p>$rhc show-app python</p><p>select and copy [524173c04382ecebeXXXe4@python-tinyblog.rhcloud.com]</p><p>$ssh 524173c04382ecebeXXXe4@python-tinyblog.rhcloud.com</p><p>&gt;&gt;&gt;OK!</p><p>[Step 02.Update Data]</p><p>Important Conception:</p><p>1.Coding locally,push your change to the server under a Git source control workflow.</p><p>2.Every OpenShift application you create has its own Git repository that only you can access.</p><p>3.If you create your application from the command line, rhc will automatically download a copy of that repository (Git calls this 'cloning') to your local system.If you create an application from the web console, you'll need to tell Git to clone the repository. Find the Git URL from the application page, and then run:</p><p>$ git clone &lt;git_url&gt; &lt;directory to create&gt;<br></p><p>&lt;$rhc show-app python&gt;</p><p>copy Git URL: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ssh://524173c04382ecebe00000e4@python-tinyblog.rhcloud.com/~/git/python.git/</p><p>$git clone <span><a href=\"http://ssh://524173c04382ecebe00000e4@python-tinyblog.rhcloud.com/~/git/python.git/\">ssh://524173c04382ecebe00000e4@python-tinyblog.rhcloud.com/~/git/python.git/</a> </span></p><p>under you current directory will create a python dir :</p><p><span>tiny@tiny-virtual-machine ~/python.blog/python $ ls -l</span></p><p><span>total 24</span></p><p><span>drwxr-xr-x 2 tiny tiny 4096 10月 &nbsp;1 23:59 data</span></p><p><span>drwxr-xr-x 2 tiny tiny 4096 10月 &nbsp;1 23:59 libs</span></p><p><span>-rw-r--r-- 1 tiny tiny 2258 10月 &nbsp;1 23:59 README</span></p><p><span>-rw-r--r-- 1 tiny tiny 2385 10月 &nbsp;1 23:59 README.md</span></p><p><span>-rwxr-xr-x 1 tiny tiny &nbsp;293 10月 &nbsp;1 23:59 setup.py</span></p><p><span>drwxr-xr-x 4 tiny tiny 4096 10月 &nbsp;1 23:59 wsgi</span></p><p>under the /wsgi/openshift dir , you'll farmilar with it's entry if you developped Django ever:</p><p><span>tiny@tiny-virtual-machine ~/python.blog/python/wsgi/openshift $ ls -l</span></p><p><span>total 160</span></p><p><span>-rw-r--r-- 1 tiny tiny &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;0 10月 &nbsp;1 23:59 __init__.py</span></p><p><span>-rwxr-xr-x 1 tiny tiny &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;503 10月 &nbsp;1 23:59 manage.py</span></p><p><span>-rw-r--r-- 1 tiny tiny &nbsp;&nbsp;3168 10月 &nbsp;1 23:59 openshiftlibs.py</span></p><p><span>-rw-r--r-- 1 tiny tiny &nbsp;&nbsp;6664 10月 &nbsp;1 23:59 settings.py</span></p><p><span>-rw-r--r-- 1 tiny tiny 135168 10月 &nbsp;2 08:45 sqlite3.db</span></p><p><span>drwxr-xr-x 3 tiny tiny &nbsp;&nbsp;4096 10月 &nbsp;1 23:59 templates</span></p><p><span>-rw-r--r-- 1 tiny tiny &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;566 10月 &nbsp;1 23:59 urls.py</span></p><p><span>-rw-r--r-- 1 tiny tiny &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;126 10月 &nbsp;1 23:59 views.py</span></p><p>So, Difference exists between Django 1.4 and the lastest one.</p><p>Then,I'll make changes !</p><p>cd to the templates\\home\\ modify the only doc home.html</p><p>cat the modified home.html:</p><p><span>tiny@tiny-virtual-machine ~/python.blog/python/wsgi/openshift/templates/home $ cat home.html </span></p><p><span>&lt;b&gt;</span><span>Yeah Django! Hello ZhangWei Sir!!!! Your success is my Happiness! ThankYou!</span></p><p><span>&lt;b&gt;</span><span>&lt;br /&gt;</span><span>let's &lt;a href=\"/admin\"&gt;admin &lt;/a&gt;</span></p><p>Once you make changes, you'll need to 'add' and 'commit' those changes - 'add' tells Git that a file or set of files will become part of a larger check in, and 'commit' completes the check in. Git requires that each commit have a message to describe it.</p><p>&lt;cd to python dir, a implicit dir .git <span>exists </span>&gt;<br></p><p>$ git add .<br></p><p>$ git commit -m \"A checkin to my application\"</p><p>Finally, you're ready to send your changes to your application - you'll 'push' these changes with:</p><p>$ git push<br></p><p>&lt;A funny Thing: All the operations executed under the VMware Linux Mint, While I doing git push, I returns 'git push ssh: Could not resolve hostname python-tinyblog.rhcloud.com: No such XXX' I checked many times and Google a lot , ends with &nbsp;failure, once I opened a Chrome tab in the VMware and typing <a href=\"http://www.google.com.hk\">www.google.com.hk</a> into the url column with a Enter, Error returns ,then I understood all the matters. With none opertation on the system network device ,I reboot the Vmware ,failed, then reboot the windows 7 and shut down the vmware, finally it's gives a Connected to the Internet , then try the git push ,OK!&gt;</p><p><span>The output of the push command will contain information from OpenShift about your deployment .</span><br></p><p>open my openShift python url :<a href=\"http://www.sparrowwei.com\">www.sparrowwei.com</a> my test url of that python Django &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;app,it returns:</p><p><img id=\"35BE2E09EB128391EABB627057557672\"><br></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>"
}
